result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffery A. Warbelton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jeffery A. Warbelton is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jeffery A. Warbelton was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

judgments.action: Guilty Due to No Contest Plea

charges.dispoDesc: Guilty Due to No Contest Plea

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Jeffery A. Warbelton

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: 4:28 p.m. Defendant Jeffery A. Warbelton in court.  Mary Margaret Sowinski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant states that his best friend is dying and he takes care of her 24/7. His truck is broken and he put $6,000 into truck. Had to pay back friends for repairs. On the way home from picking up truck - went on shoulder and broke again. Defendant receives $1,000 in disability - owes a lot of money. Court finds that defendant is unable to pay and is essentially doing community service. Court vacates judgment for assessment. Adj. 4:31 p.m.

3:24 p.m. Defendant Jeffery A. Warbelton in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State moves to dismiss Count 2 - Granted. Plea questionnaire filed. Defendant enters no contest plea.   Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty. Schiek/Burns/Court statement on sentencing. Court imposes fine and costs of $263.50. Appeal rights given. Adj. 3:30 p.m.  Review hearing scheduled for October 31, 2016 at 03:00 pm.

1:37 p.m. Defendant Jeffery A. Warbelton in court with attorney Mary L. Roth Burns.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  In receipt of complaint, waive reading - not guilty plea. Schiek/Burns statement to bond. Court sets $ sig bond. Adj. 1:39 p.m. 
  Pre-trial conference scheduled for May 3, 2016 at 03:00 pm.
